---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "Terms of use";
const description =
  "Terms of use for the National Debt Service website, including important disclaimers about advice, accuracy and links to other sites.";
---

<BaseLayout {title} {description}>
  <main id="main-content" class="bg-neutral-soft min-h-screen">
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-10 sm:py-14 space-y-7">
      <header class="space-y-3">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-trust-blue uppercase tracking-wide">
          Terms
        </p>
        <h1>Terms of use</h1>
        <p class="text-base text-slate-800 leading-relaxed">
          By using this website, you agree to these terms of use. They explain what you can expect
          from the site and what the site does and doesn’t do.
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2>Information only</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-800 leading-relaxed">
          National Debt Service is an information and signposting website. It doesn’t give you
          personal debt advice, financial advice or legal advice. Nothing on this site is intended
          to tell you what you should do in your own situation.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-800 leading-relaxed">
          For personal advice about debt, you should contact a free, regulated debt advice service
          or another qualified professional in your country.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2>Not FCA authorised</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-800 leading-relaxed">
          National Debt Service is not authorised by the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA). We don’t
          carry out regulated debt counselling or debt adjusting, and we don’t arrange or manage
          debt solutions.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2>Accuracy and changes</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-800 leading-relaxed">
          We try to keep information on this site clear and up to date. However, rules and services
          can change, and some pages may become out of date. We can’t guarantee that every detail
          will always be current, complete or accurate.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-800 leading-relaxed">
          You should always check important details directly with an official source or a regulated
          advice provider before making decisions.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2>Links to other websites</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-800 leading-relaxed">
          This site links to other organisations, such as debt advice charities, mental health
          services and official government pages. These links are provided for convenience and
          signposting only.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-800 leading-relaxed">
          We don’t control, endorse or take responsibility for the content or policies of any other
          website. Their terms and privacy policies will apply when you use them.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2>Liability</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-800 leading-relaxed">
          We can’t accept responsibility for any loss, damage or inconvenience that you may suffer
          as a result of using this site, relying on its content, or using services linked from it.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-800 leading-relaxed">
          You’re responsible for how you choose to use the information on this website and for any
          decisions you make about your own situation.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-800 leading-relaxed">
          These terms may be updated from time to time, for example if the site changes or if new
          legal requirements apply. If you carry on using the site after changes are published, it
          means you agree to the updated terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2>Contact about these terms</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-800 leading-relaxed">
          If you have questions about these terms of use, you can contact:
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold">
          <a href="mailto:contact@nationaldebtservice.co.uk">
            contact@nationaldebtservice.co.uk
          </a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
